Like the executive dysfunction still exists, but it isn’t debilitating. I don’t find myself sitting here staring at walls because my brain and body refuse to do what I need them to. This balance between overstimulated and understimulated feels much easier to navigate.

It took me longer than if I was on my medication, sure. I still get distracted easily and struggle to prioritize things in a hierarchy that makes sense. (This takes practice, I suppose.) I’ll probably always be forgetful. But I’m not angry or anxious or depressed.

And perhaps it is important to mention that I had no problem focusing on tasks this week that I normally would put off until I could take my medication. I cleaned my apartment, did loads of laundry and dishes and sat at my computer to write articles. Completing my to do lists.

What I really needed was a safe home, consistent access to healthy foods, a physical exercise I could do on my own terms, and tbh probably a therapist 😂 As well as a work environment that accommodated my body’s needs instead of forcing me to ignore them. Who knew! 😒

And I could not perform capitalism without it. Everyone in my life insisted this medication was the answer to all of my problems but I was never given support or even acknowledgment of the additional problems it created. Can’t eat, can’t sleep, can’t be present in my own life…

The key thing here though is that I felt like I needed it to function because I was to,d that I did, even when my body disagreed. I feel like my body has fought me on this every step of the way. I’ve wanted to quit it so many times but… I had to perform capitalism to eat.

This is so big for me, I’ve been in adhd medication since I was 14. It’s caused do many issues with my body, my diet, every single one of my relationships, my ability to perform at work or school… for so long I’ve felt like I needed it to function. (Like everyone else that is.)

For the last week I have not worked or taken my adhd meds. I’ve exercised daily (new for me!) and focused on eating more whole foods (also somewhat new for me.) I don’t think I’ve ever felt better or more clear headed in my life. I don’t want to numb like I usually do.

If you look into the mirror and don't see anything to love, ask yourself who's eyes you are using to look at yourself. Why their opinion is the end-all be-all of your existence, why it has the power to convince you that you wouldn't exist without their approval. (You already do.)

You deserve to be in relationships that will hold up that mirror and be like damn... Look at you! Look at your kind eyes that make me feel seen, your strong arms that make me feel safe.

We come into self-awareness by receiving love.
We learn to self-love by first being loved.

A relationship partner that asks you to bend, contort, and mutilate yourself in order to be "worthy" of love is erasing you. They're saying that the way you exist is wrong, that you shouldn't exist at all. 

But you do.
You deserve people that want to celebrate it.

How can you "just be yourself" when you are not entirely sure who You is?

There is a way that relationships act as a mirror for us to see ourselves, a way that we cannot see ourselves properly without relationships. A way that a relationship partner refusing to see us, erases us

If you can't see anything about yourself that is deserving of love, then problem is that you can't see yourself properly. Your eyes have been co-opted by someone that refuses to see you. Someone that can't. That makes it very hard to be authentic, doesn't it?

You do not need to sand down your rough edges to be loved. You do not have to paint over your scars or rework them into something acceptable. You do not have to shrink, mutilate, or cut yourself down. You don't have to perform. 

The only thing love requires is authenticity.

I encourage you to interrogate the belief you hold that you must be "worthy" of love, as if it is something you must earn or perform to achieve. That you must break yourself up into tiny bits for others to easily digest

You are not a product to be shaped for consumption.

Just because you cannot currently see things in yourself that you perceive to be "worthy" of love, doesn't meant that you aren't. It doesn't mean your loved ones are secretly lying to you or treating you like a charity case. 

What can't be seen ≠ does not exist

Your pop astrology magazine horoscope only exists so that a white man could capitalize upon it in a time where kings were running out of land to conquer. He lost his job yall lmao. Had to make something up real quick. Pop astrology is the embodiment of capitalism.

My point has been and will continue to be: pop astrology reinforces capitalism, patriarchy, & w/hite supremacy. It’s harmful, inaccurate, & misleading. It makes the entire field of astrology look easily discredible to the average person. We should ALL care & speak up on it.

But I’m going to continue to do it. We deserve to be taught how to use astrology in a way that is useful and meaningful to us. Your top search result for your zodiac sign is likely not it. But that’s where most people stop & never ask anything else about it. So I start there.

And when people come to sidereal astrology, I can’t just talk about sidereal. First I have to work to deconstruct what people think astrology is b/c their understanding of pop tropical astro is all that they have. And most don’t even know what a tropical or sidereal zodiac is.

I’m NOT saying tropical astrologers are not asking these questions. I AM saying that the pop tropical astrology you find on google doesn’t ask these questions at all & instead perpetuates harmful methods of interpretation that turn ppl off of astro altogether. It’s a problem.

Why are people associating a planet like mars, a planet of conflict, survival, and severance with sex? Why is sex considered violent? Violent for who? Why are y’all looking at the 8H of death and loss to find a sexual partner? Is sex something you inherit/obtain & not an act?

Why is a planet like the sun, associated with men, dominance, and patriarchy considered the most important planet in astrology? Why not the moon which represents our bodies? Why are we dividing planets by gender? What is gender? How has the meaning of “gender” changed over time?

Anyone who studies astrology for any period of time can look and see that historically it has been used to build and maintain empires, to conquer and oppress people. To pretend that has changed or been lost in time is foolish. We need to look deeper at it & question it more.

Or perhaps the fact that I offer up sidereal astrology as an alternative is the problem, because it challenges a lot of peoples beliefs about what astrology is, what it can do, and how it should be used. But we should question all of these things. Astrology is not free of dogma.

RT @PeoplesOracle: Knowledge without context is indoctrination… or appropriation.

Start simple with what you know. Maybe that is finger paints and a YouTube tutorial. But if you keep at it then maybe in 6m you’ve moved on to acrylics, gouache, watercolor… you don’t know yet. You haven’t tried. And time is short, so you might as well start trying now.

In that sense, even if you decide after a couple of months that it isn’t for you, you’ve still gained something from this that you didn’t have before. Self-trust, self-awareness, knowledge of a new thing that might come in handy again. And a redirect to something better.

What you’re really doing is building a relationship with yourself and developing a self-awareness of your skills, knowledge, and ability to influence things/people. Which is important because a whole lot of you have probably been told you have no influence or skills at all.

I really don’t know how to explain it, but I can tell you from experience that living your truth and trusting yourself to do it even when you have no idea if you can or if it will “work out” will change your life. Even if you fail at first. Or the first few times.

Like if you’re not taking a literal apocalypse as your cue to chase your dreams??? Or to even just look down the path and take a few steps?? You’re wasting an opportunity. Write the book! Start the blog! Buy the paint! The bike! The instrument! The knitting needles! Yes you can!

Whatever the thing is you really want to do but think you will never be good at, have the time to pursue, or won’t be worth it because you don’t think you can obtain an income doing it… NOW is the time to do it. NOW is the time to explore yourself & find out what you can do.

Loving my partner has always been easy. I love to nurture and care and observe and listen and respond. I don’t mind when I don’t understand the first time, I’ll wait & keep asking questions when they’re ready. But letting myself be loved has felt impossible before, a relief now.

I told myself I could do a lot of things I didn’t know how to do, much less have the physical capabilities and tools to do. And my parents told me this too. You can do anything, Madison. Now get away from me and go figure it out yourself.

The wound of sidereal Aries is abandonment. The planet will show you the source of this abandonment. For me it’s the Moon and my parents. The coping mechanism is overestimating your abilities. I was too young to cook for myself but I told myself I could and did anyway.

If being called “selfish” means that I am not hungry or cold or left without then so be it. I learned to not care what others thought of it very young, didn’t really have a choice. But the words still hurt to be honest because hearing it means my wounds are unseen & ignored.

And they created a child that was afraid to have things. To want and need things. They created a child that hides food in their room and keeps something beyond repair. They created a child that gives away everything they have to their own detriment. And then called it selfish.

When they called me “selfish” what they really meant was I didn’t have the ability to understand the sacrifices they made for me because my brain want developed. When they said I was greedy they were judging me for coping with the environment they forced me into.

I had two Capricorn parents that resented the fact that I had needs and that they had to put them before their own. They constantly made me feel guilty for needing things, for wanting things, for existing in a way that created labor for them. But I didn’t ask to be born!

I understand how this comes off as selfish to people who haven’t had to use this coping mechanism to survive, for people who always had enough, or people in which “sharing was caring.” But maybe sharing wasn’t caring for me. Maybe sharing was an act that created resentment.

The thing with sidereal Aries is that “selfishness” is a coping mechanism for being abandoned and discarded by your parents. There is a tendency to over estimate how much you need because you fear never having enough (again.) Better to have too much than not enough.

How long will you sit and cry outside your parents door before you finally shut up and do it yourself? How long will you wait for permission to do what needs to be done? At some point you learn to ask for forgiveness instead. And you don’t always get it.

Mutable Signs: what does your Venus say about how you discern what is real or not real in your relationships? When have you had to change your perspective to understand/be understood? Is it easy for you to be curious or is being ignorant to differences how you keep it going?

Cardinal signs: what does your Venus say about the way you’ve had to navigate power dynamics in your relationships? When have you had to relinquish control to survive? When have you had to take it? How does this inform your role in current/future relationships?
Fixed signs: what does your Venus say about WHO you’ve had to be in your relationships? What role have you had to play? Do you take this on willingly or was it to survive? Can this identity change?

So my questions for y’all are these: How is your Venus in your sidereal birth chart contributing to the story you bring to your relationships? About what experiences you’ve had & what it taught you about what you need in relationships?

Most importantly for me, I don’t have to beg to get my needs met. I may have to say exactly what I need and when, which was difficult for me at first. (No air in my chart.) But I don’t have to beg, scream or yell to be heard or acknowledged. They made me their family.

Enthusiasm because he thinks it’s really cool. Someone who answers the phone, returns my texts, and drives me to the doctor. Someone to help me when the bill is higher than I can afford. Someone who invites me everywhere, I’m always included. I got a homemade cake on my bday 🥺

And even though this may not have been something he put into words and thought about extensively I know he picked up what I was putting down. Because suddenly I had someone supporting my goal of being an astrologer and tarot reader. Someone who talked about it w strangers with

And what did he learn from those stories? That it’s important that I am included in things. That people show up for me. That people don’t make me beg to get my needs met, that I don’t feel like I have to do everything alone. That ppl like that I am different and a little weird.

Then I asked him what stories I brought to the relationship. What did I tell you about myself when you met me? What did I think was important for you to know? He said you told me about your parents, your siblings, & your best friend. I said yes that’s my Scorpio Venus 3H…

One of the most important things I learned through these stories is that acts of service are my partners love language. It’s important that he feels seen and appreciated when he does things for me like driving me to the doc, picking up the grocery bill, etc.

What does this tell me about what my partner needs? He needs someone who says exactly what they mean, someone who will take him at face value (as he interprets things this way) and someone who is honest about who they are. Don’t be vague about where you stand w them.

He told me stories about people he could “never get it right” with, no matter what he did, times when he was precise and it still bit him in the ass. When he failed to see something for what it was because he took it at face value & didn’t read between the lines.

My partner told me stories about his Virgo Venus, the way he has to be discerning about who he gets close to because he has been lied to before. Because people manipulate data and words to confuse him, the way they omit part of the story to make him draw incorrect conclusions.

This is important because the stories we bring to a new relationship tell that other person what we expect or want from a relationship. But also what we need in order to feel safe, and what to avoid in order to keep from re-opening old wounds. But it’s not always conscious.

A readers job is to inspire confidence and self-trust in their clients and encourage them to make their own decisions. Good readers want you to stand on your own, not depend on them indefinitely.

I suggest following a reader for a while and making sure your spiritual beliefs and personal values align before you spend your $. Never book with someone who inspires fear, anxiety or a fight/flight response in you w the things they do/say/post.

These are just some of the things to look out for. It’s important now more than ever that we practice discernment when looking for spiritual guidance because scammers want to capitalize on the rising popularity of these tools and the growing uncertainty & fear we are experiencing

Question they will be honest about not knowing and likely direct you to someone else that does or an external resource. 

NOTE: this does not apply if you are asking a reader inappropriate, invasive questions or for them to preform free labor for you. You’re not owed a response.

🚩 They do not answer your questions, leave you hanging, or are purposely vague and then demand money for an explanation. (Which you will probably never get.)

Readers you can trust want to help you and will be direct when giving advice. If they don’t know the answer to your

🚩 This person claims to be the *only* source for spiritual info or the only one to be able to connect to spirit. 

All human beings have the capacity to develop a relationship with spirit and their own intuitive abilities. Also, the internet, libraries & communities exist so…

NOTE: Lots of students and new readers like to start with written reports and that’s ok. But written reports should never be over $100 imo & are really limiting. Eventually you need to step up into calls or video if you’re practicing online. Don’t be shy! You can do it!

Anywhere from $100 - 300 for an hour reading. Students or newer professionals might charge $30-150 depending. But anyone asking you for $500 for 30mins or an entirely written report… you should reconsider.

🚩 They’re charging you a large, inappropriate amount of money. 

This one is a little trickier as different readers of different experience levels will charge differently. Professional astrologers with a large client base, lots of experience & good reputation can charge

Readers you can trust will direct you to their webpage or business email address to book with them & will have their process, refund policy, and disclaimers somewhere on their site so you know exactly what to expect from them.

🚩 They send you a DM saying they picked you to receive a reading or spirit guided them to you. 

Why? This is a common tactic of scammers and accounts posing as a well known reader to trick people into giving them $. You will never get your reading or it will be VERY vague.

In reality, what you likely need is a doctor, a therapist, a support group, and financial assistance. Not easy things to get, I know. But this reader isn’t helping you get them either, they’re keeping you from seeing the source of your pain so that you can’t treat it.

If anything, this mindset teaches you that you are responsible for your own suffering and not the people who are actually upholding & enforcing these systems. When you assume your suffering is a result of your own failure, you’re likely to buy a reading to see what you did wrong.

🚩 They tell you that you can manifest anything if you just believe hard enough & retrain your brain to have an abundance mindset 

Why? You cannot think/believe your way out of poverty & systems of oppression. Ignoring them doesn’t make them go away or stop them from hurting you

That you’re “ascending.” What is really happening is a slow death because you are not in tune with and meeting your bodies needs. Which could already be possible under capitalism anyway, which is why ppl looking for an answer for their suffering fall victim to these traps.

We are human beings and our existence and survival is reliant upon being present in our bodies and current life. You cannot spiritually awaken by trying to escape reality and your current life lessons. These people often list symptoms of depression and malnutrition as “signs”

🚩 They consistently talk about as “ascension” “5D” or “spiritual awakenings”

Why? While moments of spiritual enlightenment are common in life, the idea of ascending out of your body, into a higher state of being, into the astral or whatever… is a really unhealthy desire.

Scared, anxious people who have experienced great loss are likely to fall victims to these types of readers who confirm their worst fears & end up becoming dependent on a reader to tell them when they will be “safe.” But these readers will never let you feel “safe” for very long.

To strike fear and encourage anxiety in the client/audience. It’s also incredibly disrespectful to the deceased & deceased’s family to turn their grief into a way to prove yourself right & sell more readings. Is this really the kind of skills you look for in a reader? Why?

Why?

No ethically sound reader is ever going to make death predictions or use divination tools to explain death. Everyone dies and it’s unavoidable. It’s unhelpful to make these predictions as we have no control over this inevitable outcome & it only serves

🚩 They publicly make predictions surrounding the potential or recent death of someone/a group of people

🚩 They offer to make death predictions for a price
